This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it discusses the use of textual patterns and knowledge bases for automatic knowledge base construction and information extraction. It may also belong to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) because it proposes a new model for reasoning about entities and relations. Additionally, it could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) because it discusses the use of scoring functions and attention mechanisms. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category because the paper deals with extracting information from text. Finally, the paper could also be classified under databases (cs.DB) because it deals with knowledge bases.
